The independent inquiry into allegations of racism by Eskom CEO has found no evidence that André de Ruyter has conducted himself in such a manner. This comes after a senior employee wrote to board chair Malegapuru Makgoba and President Cyril Ramaphosa alleging that De Ruyter's conduct was racist and that he favoured white appointees and treated white-owned companies differently to black-owned ones. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The independent inquiry into allegations of racism by Eskom CEO has found no evidence that André de Ruyter conducted himself in such a manner. READ: Eskom wage talks collapse A senior employee alleged that De Ruyter's conduct was racist and that he favoured white appointees and treated white-owned companies differently to black-owned ones. Watch the video above for more details on this story.